{
  "texts": [
    "As a stress test, we merged from three to 777 samples, which consisted of repeating up to 259 times the HG002 family trio.",
    "This took a little more than 11 h of CPU time using Sniffles2 (11:16:18; Supplementary Table 9).",
    "Next, we applied this population/family approach of Sniffles2 across 31 ONT datasets that represented cases of Mendelian disorders in probands (seven complete trios, one duo and eight only probands).",
    "The merge was completed in 28 CPU minutes, and we measured an average of 3.89% Mendelian inconsistency rate and 1.11% of missingness (Methods, Supplementary Table 11 and Supplementary Fig. 5).",
    "The probands for sequencing were selected based on a Mendelian disease that often is caused by SVs impacting MECP2 at the Xq28 locus."
  ]
}